@node  Package mathml, Function and variable index, Top, Top
@chapter Package mathml

The @code{mathml} package is designed to convert a Maxima expression
into Presentation MathML, version 2.0.

@menu
* Definitions for package mathml::
@end menu

@node Definitions for package mathml,  , Package mathml, Package mathml
@section Definitions for package mathml

@anchor{mathml}
@deffn {Function} mathml
@*mathml (@var{expr}) @
@*mathml (@var{expr}, @var{filename_or_false}) @
@*mathml (@var{label}, @var{filename_or_false})

Convert an expression to Presentation MathML (version 2).

When the first argument is a label,
the label and its associated value are printed verbatim,
not typeset as MathML.

When the optional argument @var{filename_or_false} is supplied, any
output will be appended to the file, unless it is @code{false}, in which
case the output is returned as a string.

@code{load("mathml");} loads this package.

Examples:

@c ===beg===
@c load(mathml) $
@c mathml (integrate (sin(x), x));
@c integrate (1/(1 + x^3), x);
@c mathml (%i3);
@c mathml (%o3);
@c mathml (''%o3);
@c mathml (''%o3, "/tmp/tmp.xml");
@c mathml (''%o3, false);
@c ===end===
